<p class=3D"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"><b class=3D"ssrcss-cgjb6m-K=
eyword e2vephq0">Slaughtneil's All-Ireland club hurling semi-final against =
Loughrea will take place at Parnell Park in Dublin on Sunday, 21 December [=
13:30 GMT].</b></p><p class=3D"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">The Ulst=
er champions are bidding to reach the final for the first time in what will=
 be their sixth appearance at this stage of the competition.</p><p class=3D=
"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Parnell Park has been the venue for tw=
o of their previous five semi-finals, including their 3-15 to 3-8 loss agai=
nst Limerick's Na Piarsaigh in 2018 and their five-point defeat by Waterfor=
d's Ballygunner in 2022.</p><p class=3D"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10"=
>Paul McCormack's side retained their provincial crown with a 13-point vict=
ory over Antrim champions St John's last month, having won the Derry title =
for a 13th-straight year.</p><p class=3D"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10=
">Loughrea retained their Galway title with a one-point victory over St Tho=
mas' in November and moved straight into the All-Ireland series.</p><p clas=
s=3D"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">On the same day, Carrickmore will =
take on Mayo's Tooreen in the semi-final of the All-Ireland intermediate ch=
ampionship at Breffni Park in Cavan at 14:00.</p><p class=3D"ssrcss-1q0x1qg=
-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">The Tyrone side won the Ulster title for the first ti=
me with a six-point victory over Fermanagh's Lisbellaw on 1 December, makin=
g up for three previous defeats in the provincial final.</p><p class=3D"ssr=
css-1q0x1qg-Paragraph e1jhz7w10">Tooreen won their fifth Connacht intermedi=
ate title with victory over Galway's Meelick-Eyrecourt and are bidding to r=
